      <h1>SEO Pricing in Leeds</h1>

      <p>SEO pricing in Leeds is transparent and competitive, offering London-quality search marketing expertise at Northern prices. The cost difference is not about quality. Leeds-based consultants and agencies operate with lower overheads, and those savings pass directly to clients. A business in Headingley or Wellington Place gets the same calibre of technical analysis, content strategy, and link building that a Shoreditch agency charges twice as much to deliver.</p>

      <div class="quick-answer">
        <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> SEO packages in Leeds start at £500/month for small businesses, £1,000/month for growing companies, and £2,000+/month for enterprise. One-off audits from £500. No long-term contracts beyond an initial three-month commitment. <a href="/free-seo-audit-leeds/">Get a free audit</a> to see where you stand before committing.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Why Leeds SEO Pricing Is Different</h2>

      <p>London SEO agencies charge £2,000-£5,000 per month as standard. That pricing reflects Soho office leases, central London salaries, and the overhead of large account management teams. It does not necessarily reflect better work.</p>

      <p>Leeds has become one of the UK's strongest digital marketing hubs. The city's tech ecosystem around Leeds Dock and the wider Digital Health Hub attracts experienced SEO professionals who choose Northern quality of life over London commutes. The talent pool is deep, the experience is genuine, and the pricing reflects realistic operational costs rather than inflated metropolitan overheads.</p>

      <p>For a Leeds business, this creates a clear advantage. You work with consultants who understand the local market, know the competitive landscape across West Yorkshire, and charge rates that make SEO accessible to businesses at every stage of growth. A Roundhay independent retailer and a Trinity Leeds anchor tenant both get pricing that reflects the work involved, not the postcode of the agency.</p>

      <h2>Three Pricing Tiers</h2>

      <h3>Starter: £500 per Month</h3>

      <p>The Starter package is designed for small businesses that need professional SEO foundations without the cost of a full-service retainer. This is the right starting point for local businesses, independent shops, cafes, tradespeople, and professional services firms with a single location.</p>

      <p>What is included:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Initial technical audit:</strong> Comprehensive crawl of your website identifying technical issues, broken links, speed problems, and indexation errors.</li>
        <li><strong>On-page optimisation:</strong> Title tags, meta descriptions, heading structure, and internal linking improvements for your most important pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Business Profile optimisation:</strong> Category selection, description, attributes, photo guidance, and review strategy to improve your local pack visibility.</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly reporting:</strong> Clear report showing ranking changes, traffic trends, and work completed. No jargon, no vanity metrics.</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly strategy call (30 min):</strong> Review progress, discuss priorities, and plan the next month's focus areas.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Ideal for: Headingley cafes, Roundhay shops, sole traders, small professional services firms, local tradespeople. Businesses that need to establish a search presence and win local customers.</p>

      <h3>Growth: £1,000 per Month</h3>

      <p>The Growth package adds content strategy and link building to the Starter foundations. This is for businesses that have a functioning website and want to accelerate organic traffic growth to compete more aggressively in their market.</p>

      <p>Everything in Starter, plus:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Content strategy:</strong> Monthly content plan based on keyword research, competitor gap analysis, and search intent mapping. We identify the topics that will drive qualified traffic and outline the content needed to rank for them.</li>
        <li><strong>Content production (2 pieces/month):</strong> Two professionally written, SEO-optimised articles or landing pages per month, published directly to your site.</li>
        <li><strong>Link building:</strong> Strategic outreach to earn editorial backlinks from relevant, authoritative websites. Focus on quality over quantity, with transparent reporting on every link acquired.</li>
        <li><strong>Competitor monitoring:</strong> Monthly analysis of your competitors' SEO activity, new content, new backlinks, and ranking movements. Early warning of competitive threats and opportunities.</li>
        <li><strong>Quarterly strategy session (60 min):</strong> Deep-dive review of the overall SEO strategy, market trends, and forward planning in addition to monthly calls.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Ideal for: Wellington Place professional services firms, Leeds Dock tech companies, multi-location businesses, growing e-commerce brands. Businesses that need to outpace competitors and scale organic traffic as a primary acquisition channel.</p>

      <h3>Enterprise: £2,000+ per Month</h3>

      <p>The Enterprise package is full-service SEO for businesses where organic search is a critical revenue driver. This is a dedicated partnership with a named strategist who becomes an extension of your marketing team.</p>

      <p>Everything in Growth, plus:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Dedicated strategist:</strong> A single point of contact who learns your business, industry, and competitive landscape in depth. Not a rotating cast of junior analysts.</li>
        <li><strong>Content production (4+ pieces/month):</strong> Increased content output with a mix of long-form guides, landing pages, case studies, and thought leadership content.</li>
        <li><strong>AI search optimisation:</strong> Optimisation for AI-powered search features including Google AI Overviews, Bing Copilot, and conversational search platforms. This is the emerging frontier of SEO and increasingly critical for visibility.</li>
        <li><strong>Conversion rate optimisation (CRO):</strong> Landing page testing, call-to-action optimisation, and user journey analysis to increase the percentage of organic visitors who become leads or customers.</li>
        <li><strong>Weekly reporting:</strong> Detailed weekly updates on rankings, traffic, conversions, and work in progress. Full transparency on where time and effort are being invested.</li>
        <li><strong>Priority support:</strong> Same-day response to queries and rapid turnaround on urgent requests.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Ideal for: Financial services firms, major legal practices, large e-commerce operations, SaaS companies, multi-location brands across Yorkshire. Businesses where a 10% increase in organic traffic translates to significant revenue.</p>

      <h2>What Every Package Includes</h2>

      <p>Regardless of tier, every client receives the same commitment to transparency and professional standards.</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>No long-term lock-in:</strong> Three-month initial commitment, then month-to-month with 30 days notice. If our work is not delivering value, you should not be contractually trapped.</li>
        <li><strong>Transparent reporting:</strong> Every report shows exactly what was done, what changed, and what is planned next. No black-box tactics, no obfuscation.</li>
        <li><strong>Ethical methods only:</strong> White-hat SEO exclusively. No link schemes, no cloaking, no private blog networks. Tactics that risk Google penalties are never worth the short-term gain.</li>
        <li><strong>Direct consultant access:</strong> You communicate directly with the person doing the work, not through an account manager who relays messages.</li>
        <li><strong>Ownership of all work:</strong> Every piece of content, every technical fix, every report belongs to you. If you leave, you keep everything.</li>
      </ul>

